    "## 1. Analytical vs. Numerical Gradient Checking\n",
    "\n",
    "To verify that our analytical backprop derivatives are correct, we can compare them to a **numerical gradient** using the finite difference method:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$f'(x) \\approx \\frac{f(x + \\epsilon) - f(x - \\epsilon)}{2\\epsilon}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "def f(x):\n",
    "    return x**3 + 2*x**2 - 5*x + 1\n",
    "\n",
    "def analytical_derivative(x):\n",
    "    return 3*x**2 + 4*x - 5\n",
    "\n",
    "def numerical_derivative(x, eps=1e-5):\n",
    "    return (f(x + eps) - f(x - eps)) / (2 * eps)\n",
    "\n",
    "x_val = 2.0\n",
    "print(\"Analytical derivative at x=2.0:\", analytical_derivative(x_val))\n",
    "print(\"Numerical derivative at x=2.0:\", numerical_derivative(x_val))\n",
    "print(\"Difference:\", abs(analytical_derivative(x_val) - numerical_derivative(x_val)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
